WEBVTT

00:07.520 --> 00:14.440
[Alba] <i>In 1928, women were essentially</i>
<i>seen as accessories to be shown off...</i>

00:18.640 --> 00:21.160
<i>objects unable to express an opinion</i>
<i>or make a decision.</i>

00:22.120 --> 00:26.680
<i>Life wasn't easy for anyone,</i>
<i>but it was even harder for women.</i>

00:29.120 --> 00:31.760
<i>If you were a woman in 1928,</i>

00:31.840 --> 00:35.000
<i>freedom seemed impossible to achieve.</i>

00:35.080 --> 00:40.920
<i>To society,</i>
<i>we were just housewives and mothers.</i>

00:41.880 --> 00:44.840
<i>We didn't have the right</i>
<i>to have dreams or ambitions.</i>

00:46.480 --> 00:49.760
<i>To seek a future,</i>
<i>many women had to travel far and wide...</i>

00:51.880 --> 00:53.600
You're not going anywhere!

00:53.680 --> 00:57.480
<i>...and others had to confront the norms</i>
<i>of a backward, chauvinist society.</i>

00:57.560 --> 00:59.920
-Leave her alone!
-You stay out of this!

01:00.000 --> 01:01.000
Stay out of this!

01:02.120 --> 01:06.560
<i>In the end, all of us, rich or poor,</i>
<i>wanted the same thing:</i>

01:06.640 --> 01:08.160
<i>to be free.</i>

01:08.240 --> 01:10.960
<i>And if, to be free,</i>
<i>we had to break the law,</i>

01:11.040 --> 01:13.720
<i>we were willing to do it,</i>
<i>regardless of the consequences.</i>

01:21.640 --> 01:25.040
<i>Only those who fight for their dreams</i>
<i>can achieve them.</i>

