<i>♪ Pour salt in the wound ♪</i>

05:33.520 --> 05:39.280
[Alba] <i>The new skyscraper of the only</i>
<i>telephone company in the country.</i>

05:40.480 --> 05:44.200
<i>Thirteen floors,</i>
<i>over 30 million meters of cable,</i>

05:44.280 --> 05:47.400
<i>thousands of employees, executives,</i>
<i>switchboard operators,</i>

05:47.480 --> 05:49.840
<i>800 job openings...</i>

05:50.720 --> 05:53.920
<i>and a safe full of money to steal.</i>

05:54.000 --> 05:55.360
[Sara] Please, ladies...

05:57.040 --> 06:00.400
Welcome to the Telephone Company's
new head office.

06:01.520 --> 06:04.400
Forgive the chaos.
We're still finishing up the move.

06:04.480 --> 06:06.880
As of today,
many of the company's services

06:06.960 --> 06:10.840
as well as the city's phone connections,
will be centralized in this building.

06:10.920 --> 06:13.000
So I ask you to pay attention.

06:13.080 --> 06:14.360
CHAPTER 1: DREAMS

06:14.440 --> 06:19.000
Candidates for switchboard operators,
line up on the left and state your names.

06:20.640 --> 06:23.160
Welcome to the Telephone Company.
Can I help you?

06:23.240 --> 06:25.840
-Yes, I'm here for the tests.
-For switchboard operator.

06:25.920 --> 06:27.480
Tell me your name. I'll check the list.

06:27.560 --> 06:29.040
-Lidia.
-Lidia?

06:29.120 --> 06:30.560
-Lidia Aguilar.
-Aguilar.

06:32.280 --> 06:35.160
I'm sorry, you're not on the short list.

06:35.240 --> 06:38.840
-Short list? I thought we just came--
-You're not the only one.

06:38.920 --> 06:42.320
They were inundated with applications,
so they made a short list.

06:43.680 --> 06:46.760
-I'm sorry, Lidia. Thanks for coming.
-Oh, well.

06:46.840 --> 06:47.960
Your name is?

06:49.600 --> 06:50.720
Lidia Aguilar.

06:53.920 --> 06:56.240
The tests begin at twelve o'clock.

06:56.320 --> 06:59.160
Anyone not inside the hall by then
won't be participating.

06:59.240 --> 07:02.360
There are 390 applications
for just 12 positions.

07:02.440 --> 07:06.320
Twelve fortunate women will be getting
the best job of their lives.

07:06.400 --> 07:07.800
So look sharp.

07:07.880 --> 07:09.280
Follow me, please.

07:10.880 --> 07:13.920
You're in Madrid's most modern building.

07:14.000 --> 07:16.840
Thirteen floors devoted
to the Telephone Company.

07:17.760 --> 07:21.800
On the first floor,
reception and the sales department.

07:22.400 --> 07:25.920
<i>On the fourth and fifth floors,</i>
<i>administrative services.</i>

07:26.000 --> 07:28.120
<i>On the sixth and seventh floors,</i>
<i>the switchboard rooms,</i>

07:28.200 --> 07:30.840
<i>where chosen applicants</i>
<i>will have the privilege of working.</i>

07:31.400 --> 07:37.040
<i>Next, two floors with the machine rooms,</i>
<i>maintenance and the engineering offices.</i>

07:37.600 --> 07:40.960
Above this are the floors
for events and meetings.

07:41.040 --> 07:44.960
And finally,
management offices are on the 13th floor

07:47.160 --> 07:49.440
TELEPHONE COMPANY

07:51.040 --> 07:52.160
MANAGEMENT OFFICE

07:59.560 --> 08:01.520
-Thank you.
-Thank you, Mr. Cifuentes.

08:02.800 --> 08:04.280
Excuse me.

08:32.799 --> 08:35.760
Miss, what are you doing here?

08:37.280 --> 08:39.240
I'm here for the operator tests.

08:39.320 --> 08:43.440
Someone said they were here,
but I don't see anybody!

08:44.000 --> 08:47.240
[chuckles] They're here
if you're a man in a suit

08:47.320 --> 08:50.120
looking to be an accounts executive,
which you aren't.

08:50.200 --> 08:52.080
Switchboard tests are on the sixth floor.

08:52.160 --> 08:56.280
The doors close in two minutes.
And a word of warning...

08:56.360 --> 08:57.720
Punctuality comes first here.

08:57.800 --> 08:59.440
-Thank you.
-[chuckles]

09:01.600 --> 09:03.480
All right. Ricardo Rodríguez?

09:04.840 --> 09:07.760
Uh, honey, you'd better take the stairs.

09:10.280 --> 09:11.360
[chuckles]

09:23.360 --> 09:24.960
[both yelp]

09:26.960 --> 09:29.400
They shut the door. We've been left out.

09:29.480 --> 09:31.360
The tests started at 12:00.

09:31.440 --> 09:34.080
I got lost three times in the subway.

09:34.160 --> 09:35.920
[Ángeles] No, you can't...

09:37.640 --> 09:38.640
Yes?

09:38.720 --> 09:41.440
Excuse me, we're here
for the switchboard operator tests.

09:41.520 --> 09:43.080
-You're late.
-I know.

09:43.720 --> 09:45.800
I know punctuality comes first
in this company.

09:45.880 --> 09:47.480
Then why did you knock?

09:49.800 --> 09:52.600
To find out if understanding comes second.

09:56.600 --> 09:57.440
Look at her.

09:58.960 --> 10:01.440
Straight from the station
with her suitcase.

10:01.520 --> 10:04.360
-Six hundred kilometers to get here.
-Five hundred and fifty.

10:04.440 --> 10:05.320
Yeah.

10:06.520 --> 10:09.320
And because she was one minute late,
she'll go home empty-handed.

10:10.800 --> 10:14.160
It's my fault... Miss Millán.

10:16.200 --> 10:17.800
[stammers] I'm sorry.

10:19.080 --> 10:23.280
I offered to accompany them
since I was bringing you these papers,

10:23.840 --> 10:25.640
and I got the floors mixed up.

10:25.720 --> 10:27.560
-You got the floors mixed up?
-Yes.

10:28.440 --> 10:30.640
Your first mistake
since you started working for me.

10:30.720 --> 10:33.280
As you see,
our workers are very understanding.

10:33.360 --> 10:34.760
But, unfortunately for you,

10:34.840 --> 10:37.080
Ángeles doesn't decide
if you get through this door.

10:37.160 --> 10:38.240
I do.

10:47.960 --> 10:49.840
-Thank you.
-Yes, thank you.

10:49.920 --> 10:52.080
If I went back to the village
without doing the tests--

10:52.160 --> 10:53.760
-Ángeles, isn't it?
-Mm-hmm.

10:53.840 --> 10:56.840
With a name like that,
you must be our guardian angel.

10:56.920 --> 10:59.560
I wouldn't say that. [chuckles]

11:00.760 --> 11:02.200
Sorry. Over here.

11:03.920 --> 11:04.800
Excuse me.

11:06.400 --> 11:09.640
Would there be a way to pass the tests
without taking them?

11:09.720 --> 11:10.560
No.

11:10.640 --> 11:11.920
Good morning.

11:13.400 --> 11:14.280
Ladies.

11:18.840 --> 11:21.000
I see this is going to be
a great day for the company.

11:21.880 --> 11:23.400
Are you all here for the tests?

11:24.680 --> 11:26.640
It's going to be very hard to choose.

11:27.560 --> 11:30.320
If only we could buy more switchboards
and give you all jobs.

11:30.400 --> 11:32.200
-[Ángeles chuckles]
-[pencil clatters]

11:38.320 --> 11:39.400
Thank you.

11:39.920 --> 11:43.400
I don't want to make you
more nervous than you already are,

11:43.480 --> 11:46.440
so good luck to all of you.

11:47.280 --> 11:49.280
[inaudible]

11:56.400 --> 12:00.880
<i>♪ Don't wanna be mistaken</i>
<i>Don't wanna feel my heart breaking ♪</i>

12:00.960 --> 12:05.800
<i>♪ But I can't get enough, oh!</i>
<i>Of your sweet love, oh! ♪</i>

12:05.880 --> 12:10.480
<i>♪ Feel my heart racing, anticipating ♪</i>

12:10.560 --> 12:15.080
<i>♪ Counting every minute, oh!</i>
<i>And I want you in it, oh! ♪</i>

12:15.160 --> 12:19.320
<i>♪ Don't tell me, baby</i>
<i>What I'm feeling ain't right ♪</i>

12:20.120 --> 12:24.640
<i>♪ Let's get down on the floor</i>
<i>And do it tonight ♪</i>

12:26.200 --> 12:29.360
<i>♪ Right now keep it sexy ♪</i>

12:30.600 --> 12:31.760
<i>♪ Oh, yeah ♪</i>

12:32.920 --> 12:33.840
<i>♪ Keep it sexy ♪</i>

12:35.680 --> 12:39.520
Remedios Fuentes, selected.
Lucía Villar, not selected.

12:39.600 --> 12:42.840
Marta Rodríguez, selected.
Laura Sarmiento, selected.

12:42.920 --> 12:46.480
Verónica Sánchez, selected.
Ángeles Montes, not selected.

12:46.560 --> 12:48.880
Carlota Rodríguez de Senillosa, selected.

12:48.960 --> 12:50.520
María José Pando, selected.

12:50.600 --> 12:53.440
María Inmaculada Suárez, selected.

12:54.760 --> 12:57.360
Congratulations to all those chosen.

12:58.760 --> 12:59.840
Excuse me.

13:00.760 --> 13:02.840
Sorry, my name wasn't called.

13:03.480 --> 13:07.240
-You didn't pass.
-What? I'd like to see the list.

13:07.320 --> 13:10.160
The results are not public,
but they are fair.

13:10.240 --> 13:12.600
-I am entitled to--
-You aren't entitled to anything!

13:12.680 --> 13:14.720
You didn't pass, period.

13:14.840 --> 13:15.920
[Carlos] Is there a problem?

13:28.640 --> 13:29.840
[inhales deeply]

13:30.760 --> 13:32.840
Miss Aguilar, which academy did you go to?

13:32.920 --> 13:34.720
-None. I'm self-taught.
-Self-taught?

13:34.800 --> 13:36.480
-Yes.
-[chuckles]

13:36.560 --> 13:38.800
Haven't you ever studied anything
on your own?

13:38.880 --> 13:41.080
To be honest, I've never studied.

13:42.520 --> 13:43.960
But don't tell my father.

13:44.040 --> 13:47.440
I wouldn't want him to think
he wasted his money on my boarding school.

13:52.160 --> 13:54.840
I imagine that,
after doing well on the tests,

13:54.920 --> 13:56.960
you don't know why you weren't chosen.

13:57.040 --> 13:58.360
It's your arms.

13:59.720 --> 14:01.840
-What?
-They're not long enough.

14:02.520 --> 14:04.560
There are many subscribers,
the switchboards are big,

14:04.640 --> 14:07.360
and sometimes an operator has
to handle two switchboards.

14:08.200 --> 14:09.480
If I may say...

14:11.240 --> 14:14.040
You're two centimeters under the minimum.

14:15.280 --> 14:19.760
If I may be so bold, Don Carlos,
this requirement is nonsense.

14:20.240 --> 14:22.800
-Excuse me?
-Trinidad Seijo,

14:22.880 --> 14:24.920
the operator in my hometown,

14:25.000 --> 14:27.840
did the whole county,
almost 300 subscribers,

14:27.920 --> 14:29.120
all with one hand.

14:30.040 --> 14:31.360
She only had one hand.

14:32.880 --> 14:35.520
So it's not the length, it's the skill.

14:39.840 --> 14:41.160
Why do you want to be an operator?

14:41.240 --> 14:44.760
You want me to say
it's the greatest job in the world.

14:44.840 --> 14:48.080
But we both know I'd be lying.

14:50.120 --> 14:51.720
Your job is much better.

14:51.800 --> 14:54.400
But, unfortunately,
I'm told it isn't available.

14:54.680 --> 14:57.120
A woman with character,
the gift of the gab and a sense of humor.

14:57.200 --> 14:59.880
Not the first one you've met, I'm sure.

14:59.960 --> 15:01.600
I've met a few...

15:02.720 --> 15:04.200
but I don't know if any were like you.

15:05.040 --> 15:06.320
No, they weren't.

15:10.520 --> 15:12.640
Carolina, see the lady downstairs.

15:14.000 --> 15:16.360
Tell Sara she's on the list.

15:16.440 --> 15:18.400
-Welcome aboard, Miss Aguilar.
-Thank you.

15:18.480 --> 15:20.720
The next time
you want to impress a manager,

15:20.800 --> 15:22.520
don't tell him you want to take his job.

15:22.600 --> 15:25.080
And the next time
you want to impress a woman,

15:25.160 --> 15:28.560
don't make her feel you're only interested
in her measurements.

15:32.280 --> 15:34.600
The wouldn't-hurt-a-fly act worked.

15:35.960 --> 15:38.640
Excuse me? I don't know what you mean.

15:38.720 --> 15:43.480
The goody-two-shoes act may work
on Sara and Carlos, but not on me.

15:43.560 --> 15:44.760
I'll be watching you.

15:48.960 --> 15:51.480
Honey, you'd better take the stairs.

15:57.560 --> 15:58.760
[chuckles softly]

16:02.800 --> 16:04.880
-[lines ringing]
-[indistinct chatter]

16:05.800 --> 16:08.680
[Ángeles] Good afternoon.
Operator three. How may I help you?

16:10.280 --> 16:11.560
One moment, please.

16:19.360 --> 16:23.480
Central here. You have a call from 235.

16:23.560 --> 16:24.840
Do you wish to take it?

16:25.560 --> 16:26.720
Thank you.

16:27.120 --> 16:29.200
[Sara] Thanks, Ángeles.
That's enough for now.

16:29.280 --> 16:32.240
Ángeles knows the company
and her job better than anyone else.

16:32.320 --> 16:35.920
[Alba] <i>The operator who knows this company</i>
<i>and her job better than anyone else.</i>

16:36.640 --> 16:41.320
<i>If anyone could tell me</i>
<i>all I needed to know to rob the safe,</i>

16:41.400 --> 16:42.360
<i>it was Ángeles.</i>

16:42.440 --> 16:44.320
There are three shifts:
morning, day, and night.

16:45.080 --> 16:47.920
<i>I'd have to get close to her</i>
<i>and get her to trust me enough</i>

16:48.000 --> 16:51.320
<i>to tell me the secrets</i>
<i>of the Telephone Company.</i>

16:51.800 --> 16:55.120
[Sara] When you hear the gong, it's time
to change positions, is that clear?

16:55.840 --> 16:58.640
Good. Now, if you'll excuse me,

16:58.720 --> 17:00.720
the company director
wants to introduce himself.

17:02.000 --> 17:04.680
Don Francisco, the new employees.

17:04.760 --> 17:05.880
Marta Rodríguez...

17:05.960 --> 17:10.599
-Isn't Carlos Cifuentes the director?
-He's the owner's son.

17:10.680 --> 17:13.000
-[Sara] María Inmaculada Suárez.
-Who's the director?

17:13.920 --> 17:14.960
[Sara] Laura Sarmiento.

17:16.640 --> 17:17.720
Petra Silva.

17:18.880 --> 17:20.040
Lourdes Trapero.

17:21.079 --> 17:22.880
This is Raquel Levante.

17:23.880 --> 17:25.680
Remedios Fuentes.

17:26.319 --> 17:28.160
Carlota Rodríguez de Senillosa.

17:29.360 --> 17:30.920
Lidia Aguilar.

17:31.480 --> 17:32.480
Alba.

17:34.400 --> 17:36.920
I'm sorry, but you've mistaken me
for someone else.

17:37.800 --> 17:40.200
My name's Lidia Aguilar.
Pleased to meet you.

17:42.720 --> 17:44.200
I'm sorry, Miss Aguilar.

17:45.400 --> 17:47.160
You reminded me of an old friend.

17:48.240 --> 17:49.360
Don't worry.

17:51.720 --> 17:53.280
[Sara] María José Pando.

17:57.120 --> 17:58.960
[young Francisco] <i>Come on, Alba!</i>

17:59.040 --> 18:00.240
Run!

18:00.320 --> 18:02.320
Pass me the suitcase!

18:02.400 --> 18:03.440
TEN YEARS EARLIER

18:03.520 --> 18:05.160
[young Alba] <i>I can't believe</i>
<i>we're going to Madrid.</i>

18:05.760 --> 18:07.760
-Do you regret it?
-Are you crazy?

18:07.840 --> 18:08.840
[Francisco chuckles]

18:08.920 --> 18:11.760
I'm thinking of all
I'll do when I get there,

18:11.840 --> 18:12.960
like finding a job.

18:13.040 --> 18:17.320
Then I'll save a lot of money.
I'll buy a beautiful dress

18:17.400 --> 18:19.720
and go to an open-air dance
and order a White Lady.

18:19.800 --> 18:23.520
-A White Lady?
-Of course. It's what city girls drink.

18:23.600 --> 18:25.240
[chuckles]

18:25.320 --> 18:27.120
-What are you going to do?
-Me?

18:27.200 --> 18:30.120
I'm going to kiss that lovely birthmark
on your neck.

18:34.240 --> 18:36.040
[train whistle sounding]

18:43.560 --> 18:45.560
Hey! My suitcase! Hey!

18:53.880 --> 18:56.400
-Hey! Hey, you thief! That's my suitcase!
-No, it's mine!

18:56.480 --> 18:57.480
Listen, I...

18:59.040 --> 19:01.320
Let go of me! Francisco!

19:01.400 --> 19:03.520
<i>Francisco!</i>

19:15.320 --> 19:17.040
[phone ringing]

19:19.280 --> 19:22.480
-I told you not to call me here.
-[Alba] <i>It's an emergency, Beltrán.</i>

19:22.560 --> 19:24.400
A problem's come up.

19:24.480 --> 19:28.920
I can't do the heist I planned.
I need another place... and more time.

19:29.000 --> 19:31.080
Don't give me your life story.

19:31.160 --> 19:34.640
You know the penalty for murder? Death.

19:34.720 --> 19:36.720
<i>You have one day to avoid it.</i>

19:37.640 --> 19:39.560
<i>Tomorrow at 1:00, in the park.</i>

19:41.560 --> 19:44.840
Carlota, do you know how to get here?

19:45.800 --> 19:48.360
Dolores' Boardinghouse on Blancaró.

19:48.440 --> 19:50.280
Yes, you can't miss it.

19:50.360 --> 19:53.640
Go straight ahead,
take the third street on the left--

19:53.720 --> 19:56.640
-[Miguel] It's the <i>second</i> on the left.
-Says who?

19:56.720 --> 20:00.720
Miguel Pascual, communications engineer.

20:01.240 --> 20:04.040
Madrid born and bred.
I know the city blindfolded.

20:04.120 --> 20:07.280
[laughs] Did you hear, Marga?
A versatile man.

20:07.360 --> 20:08.760
Not many of those around.

20:08.840 --> 20:10.600
-I agree.
-[gasps]

20:11.600 --> 20:12.640
[chuckles]

20:12.720 --> 20:15.720
-This is Miguel.
-[stammers] Oh, he's your boyfriend.

20:15.800 --> 20:19.040
Don't say that word in front of her.
She's allergic to it.

20:19.120 --> 20:22.400
[chuckles] I'm going to the bar
across the street later. You coming?

20:22.480 --> 20:23.920
I'll finish up and see you there.

20:25.720 --> 20:29.720
Lidia, are you coming to the bar with us?

20:29.800 --> 20:31.840
No, I've got things to do.

20:31.920 --> 20:33.120
[Marga] Can I come?

20:33.200 --> 20:35.760
It's to thank Ángeles
for what she did for us.

20:36.560 --> 20:37.680
Ángeles is going?

20:37.760 --> 20:41.600
Yes, she left her daughter
with a neighbor. Are you coming?

20:41.680 --> 20:42.720
[Ángeles] Good evening.

20:44.240 --> 20:46.800
The Cifuentes family made
a huge investment

20:46.880 --> 20:48.800
in erecting this building.

20:48.880 --> 20:51.080
Naturally, they want to increase security.

20:51.160 --> 20:53.280
We only have access during our shift.

20:53.360 --> 20:55.200
They have to be careful.

20:55.280 --> 20:56.880
Everything goes through head office.

20:56.960 --> 21:00.720
Company earnings, payroll...
Basically everything.

21:00.800 --> 21:02.760
[Marga] Grandma,
you're going to make me deaf!

21:02.840 --> 21:05.400
See? You're worth your weight in gold.

21:05.480 --> 21:07.160
<i>Just wait till I tell Rosario...</i>

21:07.240 --> 21:10.360
Grandma, before you say anything...

21:11.760 --> 21:14.000
I've been thinking about it and...

21:15.000 --> 21:17.720
I should turn down the job
and go back to the village.

21:17.800 --> 21:20.080
What? Are you crazy?

21:21.240 --> 21:22.920
We're not a rich family,

21:23.000 --> 21:24.760
and you haven't got a husband
to support you.

21:24.840 --> 21:27.520
<i>I won't let you stay here</i>
<i>for the rest of your life</i>

21:27.600 --> 21:29.800
<i>looking after an old lady.</i>

21:29.880 --> 21:33.360
<i>You gave up enough for your mother.</i>
<i>God rest her soul.</i>

21:33.440 --> 21:34.920
Sure, Grandma...

21:35.960 --> 21:38.680
but I was happy with you and my mother.

21:38.760 --> 21:42.440
She was with you, too.
But you have to look out for yourself now.

21:42.520 --> 21:45.040
<i>For once in your life,</i>
<i>think just about yourself,</i>

21:45.120 --> 21:46.160
<i>not everyone else.</i>

21:46.240 --> 21:48.720
I know. And I am, but...

21:50.800 --> 21:54.680
-the capital's too big for me.
-Fear passes, Marga.

21:56.440 --> 21:58.440
And so does life
if you don't make the most of it.

21:58.520 --> 22:00.720
<i>-Don't forget that.</i>
-Thanks.

22:02.280 --> 22:05.520
I have to go, Grandma.

22:05.840 --> 22:08.400
Take care. [kisses] I love you.

22:11.960 --> 22:13.160
[sighs]

22:13.800 --> 22:15.440
-That's a lot of money.
-[Carlota] Hey...

22:15.520 --> 22:17.960
Stop talking shop, and let's have a toast.

22:18.040 --> 22:19.120
Vermouth.

22:19.680 --> 22:21.440
But vermouth has alcohol in it.

22:21.520 --> 22:25.120
[laughs] Yes, but you can order
something else if you like.

22:26.600 --> 22:28.480
No, that's okay.

22:29.560 --> 22:31.920
Maybe it's too strong for me, too.

22:32.000 --> 22:34.320
I haven't had one since...
I can't remember.

22:34.400 --> 22:36.800
I haven't been in a bar
since I got pregnant.

22:36.880 --> 22:39.520
It'll prepare you for the champagne
at the party tonight.

22:39.600 --> 22:40.600
[Marga] What party?

22:40.680 --> 22:43.760
-[Carlota] The grand opening party.
-[Ángeles] Everyone's going.

22:43.840 --> 22:45.640
I can't go. I need to watch my daughter.

22:45.720 --> 22:49.480
But the operators are going,
the clerks, even the bosses...

22:49.560 --> 22:51.560
The Cifuenteses are mingling
with the workers. Sure.

22:51.640 --> 22:54.720
-It's about time!
-I can't go.

22:54.800 --> 22:56.480
I don't like parties much.

22:56.560 --> 22:59.680
[scoffs] To say you don't like parties,

22:59.760 --> 23:02.280
you have to have gone
to at least one in your life.

23:02.360 --> 23:05.160
[laughs] And you look
like you've never been to any!

23:05.240 --> 23:08.120
Come on, let's toast. Come on, Lidia.

23:08.200 --> 23:12.040
Let's toast to Marga
and her first vermouth.

23:12.120 --> 23:16.080
To Ángeles, because she helped us
get this opportunity.

23:16.160 --> 23:19.080
-And to the new cable girls.
-[Ángeles] Yes!

23:22.040 --> 23:25.480
Ah! And because
we're now independent women.

23:25.560 --> 23:26.720
[man] Carlota.

23:30.640 --> 23:33.840
Get your things
and come with me right now.

23:33.920 --> 23:36.920
No. I don't have to go anywhere.

23:37.000 --> 23:39.120
I have a job
and I'm an independent woman.

23:41.560 --> 23:43.480
Let go of me.
I'm not one of your soldiers!

23:43.560 --> 23:44.640
Let go of me!

23:45.280 --> 23:46.840
-[Miguel] Don Emilio--
-Stay out of it.

23:46.920 --> 23:48.480
You're nothing to this family.

23:48.560 --> 23:50.120
You'll have to force me.

23:50.200 --> 23:55.000
[Emilio] You thought I wouldn't find out?
When did you become a liar?

23:55.080 --> 23:57.360
[Carlota] Since you stopped caring
about what I want.

23:57.440 --> 24:00.320
I don't want a husband.
I want a job and to be independent.

24:00.400 --> 24:05.120
A girl of your class doesn't work.
Stop this nonsense and get in the car.

24:06.760 --> 24:07.840
I said get in!

24:08.480 --> 24:09.680
[all gasp]

24:12.400 --> 24:14.080
Yes, sir, Colonel.

24:20.320 --> 24:22.320
[stuttering] So that's...

24:22.400 --> 24:23.760
Carlota's father, yes.

24:26.800 --> 24:30.720
Well, I'd better go home.
My husband's waiting for me.

24:30.800 --> 24:32.760
-Can you find the boardinghouse?
-Yes.

24:32.840 --> 24:35.720
Carlota told me how to get
from here to Blancaró Street.

24:35.800 --> 24:38.320
-Good. See you tomorrow.
-See you tomorrow.

24:38.400 --> 24:40.840
Ángeles! Wait, I'll go with you.

24:45.800 --> 24:48.640
Let the champagne flow
and get whatever the gentlemen need!

24:49.360 --> 24:51.840
I assume you're here because you did it.

24:51.920 --> 24:55.520
I got the job,
and I know where the safe is.

24:55.600 --> 24:57.560
But there's a problem. I saw Francisco.

24:57.640 --> 24:59.360
-[Victoria] Francisco?
-[Alba] <i>My</i> Francisco.

24:59.440 --> 25:01.640
-[Victoria] What?
-He's the company director.

25:01.720 --> 25:03.360
-[Victoria] Did he see you?
-Yes.

25:03.440 --> 25:06.120
[Victoria] You have to get out of there
right away.

25:06.200 --> 25:09.480
[Alba] I can't. If I don't pay what I owe,
I'll be convicted.

25:11.400 --> 25:14.160
[Victoria] If I had that money...

25:14.240 --> 25:15.960
You know me.

25:16.880 --> 25:18.200
Victoria, I'm doing it tonight.

25:19.000 --> 25:22.960
One of the girls said
that there's security, but I can do it.

25:23.880 --> 25:26.400
I'll go to the party, get the keys,
take the money,

25:26.480 --> 25:28.680
and tomorrow I'll be far away from here.

25:29.600 --> 25:31.000
And from Francisco.

25:32.280 --> 25:36.200
-Alba, I think--
-I just have to be quick.

25:37.520 --> 25:39.200
If I see him, I'll give him the slip.

25:40.280 --> 25:43.680
Alba, rushing things is never wise.

25:43.760 --> 25:45.040
It's crazy.

25:46.360 --> 25:48.360
It's either that or the garrote.

25:50.040 --> 25:51.040
Ah!

25:53.840 --> 25:55.160
Room 27.

25:55.240 --> 25:56.280
Come here.

25:58.440 --> 26:02.960
Alba, honey, I've already lost Gimena.
I wouldn't want to lose you, too.

26:24.120 --> 26:27.320
Dinner is at 8:30,
and the door is locked at 11:00.

26:27.400 --> 26:29.680
I know I needn't worry
about your behavior.

26:29.760 --> 26:32.720
Your grandmother assured me
that you're a responsible girl.

26:32.800 --> 26:36.480
This is a decent boardinghouse,
and now it's your home.

26:36.560 --> 26:37.560
Come.

26:41.360 --> 26:45.200
Here. There are sheets on the bed,

26:45.280 --> 26:49.240
and there's a set of towels
you can use until you buy your own.

26:49.320 --> 26:51.360
-Good night.
-Doña Lola...

26:51.440 --> 26:56.720
tonight is the company's opening party.
They've invited the new operators.

26:56.800 --> 26:58.960
I promise I'll be back
before you lock the door.

26:59.040 --> 27:01.040
Very well. Be careful.

27:01.120 --> 27:05.600
There's always some swine waiting
to take advantage of a decent girl.

27:05.680 --> 27:08.600
You know, "open mind, closed legs."

27:08.680 --> 27:10.320
-Good night.
-Good night.

27:20.200 --> 27:22.640
-[laughing] What?
-Come here!

27:22.720 --> 27:24.520
You're talking
to the new chief technician

27:24.600 --> 27:28.200
for the head office of the country's
largest telephone company.

27:29.600 --> 27:33.120
-When did it happen?
-Francisco told me this afternoon.

27:33.200 --> 27:34.520
I almost hugged that stuffed shirt!

27:34.600 --> 27:36.520
-Mario!
-What, honey?

27:36.600 --> 27:38.640
I'm just saying what everyone thinks.

27:38.720 --> 27:40.240
-Wonderful!
-We'll pay off the house.

27:40.320 --> 27:42.520
You'll stop working.
Our problems are over.

27:42.600 --> 27:44.480
You understand? You understand, honey?

27:45.400 --> 27:46.920
I love you. Let's celebrate.

27:49.240 --> 27:50.880
I'm so happy!

27:50.960 --> 27:52.040
Yes.

27:52.120 --> 27:56.200
-Mario, you want me to stop working?
-That's what we talked about.

27:57.400 --> 27:58.280
Well, yeah.

27:58.360 --> 28:00.080
Yes, we did, but...

28:02.880 --> 28:05.440
that was before, and...

28:06.320 --> 28:08.160
Mario, I love my job.

28:10.360 --> 28:13.520
More than being at home
with your husband and daughter?

28:13.600 --> 28:17.720
No, you two are my priority. Always.

28:17.800 --> 28:21.960
If we're your priority, what are you doing
drinking vermouth while we're at home?

28:22.040 --> 28:24.520
God, it was the first time in three years.

28:31.240 --> 28:32.480
Mario...

28:38.520 --> 28:40.080
[door slams]

28:40.160 --> 28:41.360
[sighs]

28:49.440 --> 28:50.960
Aren't you coming down for supper?

28:52.960 --> 28:55.160
We're doing this for your own good.

28:55.880 --> 28:59.120
Have you stopped to think
that it might not be what's best for me?

29:09.240 --> 29:11.240
[upbeat music playing]

29:19.040 --> 29:21.400
<i>♪ Shut up, let us have fun ♪</i>

29:21.480 --> 29:23.760
<i>♪ Rock up like we're so punk ♪</i>

29:23.840 --> 29:26.160
<i>♪ We're living the good life ♪</i>

29:27.400 --> 29:28.560
<i>♪ Good life ♪</i>

29:28.640 --> 29:30.960
<i>♪ Good nights become good times ♪</i>

29:31.040 --> 29:33.400
<i>♪ We'll stay up the whole night ♪</i>

29:33.480 --> 29:35.920
<i>♪ We're living the good life ♪</i>

29:36.880 --> 29:38.160
<i>♪ Good life ♪</i>

29:46.520 --> 29:48.520
[Marga] My goodness,
there are so many people here.

29:48.600 --> 29:51.080
Eight hundred workers.
If even a quarter came...

29:51.160 --> 29:53.920
I knew I couldn't miss this! [chuckling]

29:54.000 --> 29:56.280
[Marga] I still can't believe you're here.

29:56.360 --> 30:00.240
When your father came into the bar,
I almost got in the car, I was so scared.

30:00.320 --> 30:02.560
Do you know
what a woman's worst enemy is?

30:02.640 --> 30:03.640
Submission.

30:04.520 --> 30:08.400
-I was always taught to obey.
-Sure. Me, too.

30:08.480 --> 30:11.080
"A woman needs to always be proper
and obedient, Carlota."

30:11.160 --> 30:12.520
But one day I thought,

30:12.600 --> 30:15.120
"You're not a woman.
How do you know what I need?"

30:15.200 --> 30:17.600
So he can lock all the doors he wants.

30:17.680 --> 30:20.440
"There is no gate, no lock, no bolt

30:20.520 --> 30:22.240
that you can set upon
the freedom of my mind."

30:23.000 --> 30:24.400
Virginia Woolf said that.

30:25.000 --> 30:26.440
Is she a friend of yours?

30:27.080 --> 30:28.880
[crowd applauding]

30:31.200 --> 30:32.960
[Carmen] It's not as if we're royalty.

30:33.040 --> 30:35.840
Since when do you mind
being the center of attention?

30:35.920 --> 30:37.760
Who said I minded?

30:37.840 --> 30:40.400
Will anything ever be good enough for you?

30:40.480 --> 30:43.880
I thought marrying you was good enough.
At first.

30:43.960 --> 30:45.800
I'm going to mingle. See you soon.

30:50.480 --> 30:54.360
<i>-♪ I'm Dr. Jekyll and I'm Mr. Hyde ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Mr. Hyde ♪</i>

30:54.440 --> 30:58.360
<i>-♪ I wanna speak, but I'm tongue-tied ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Tongue-tied ♪</i>

30:58.440 --> 31:02.520
<i>♪ I'm wide awake</i>
<i>In this dream that I can't... ♪</i>

31:02.600 --> 31:03.720
[women laughing]

31:03.800 --> 31:06.360
<i>♪ No, I can't escape ♪</i>

31:06.840 --> 31:11.040
<i>♪ Wanna feel you on the inside</i>
<i>Come and make me wide-eyed ♪</i>

31:11.120 --> 31:14.960
<i>-♪ And you tell me it's okay ♪</i>
<i>-♪ That you do what you do ♪</i>

31:15.040 --> 31:19.160
<i>♪ Make me feel like I'm so high</i>
<i>I think I'm losing my mind ♪</i>

31:19.240 --> 31:22.720
<i>-♪ And you tell me it's okay ♪</i>
<i>-♪ That you do what you do ♪</i>

31:24.200 --> 31:25.520
Good evening.

31:26.240 --> 31:29.120
-Excuse me.
-Miss... What was it?

31:31.520 --> 31:33.800
-Aguilar. [chuckles]
-Aguilar, that's it.

31:33.880 --> 31:35.440
[Carlos] What a pleasant surprise.

31:35.520 --> 31:38.440
So I see. You were having
a terrible time until I arrived.

31:38.520 --> 31:41.800
Ah! I haven't had time.
And one must be nice to the staff.

31:41.880 --> 31:43.920
Is that what you're doing?
Being nice?

31:44.000 --> 31:47.240
Some things you do out of obligation,
others you do for pleasure.

31:47.320 --> 31:49.040
Clearly, this is the latter.

31:52.360 --> 31:54.680
I see the party is turning out to be fun.

31:55.400 --> 31:57.640
Miss Aguilar, Francisco Gómez.

31:57.720 --> 31:59.520
-We met earlier.
-Yes.

32:00.600 --> 32:02.120
-A drink?
-No, thank you.

32:02.200 --> 32:04.640
A White Lady? A city girl's drink.

32:04.720 --> 32:06.920
This night deserves a toast.

32:07.000 --> 32:09.960
Thanks, but I don't like White Ladies.

32:10.040 --> 32:14.200
Now that's what I call honesty!
Not a common quality.

32:14.280 --> 32:16.600
Luckily, Miss Aguilar has
more than enough for both of us.

32:16.680 --> 32:18.160
Along with other virtues.

32:19.080 --> 32:20.120
-Such as?
-[music stops]

32:22.640 --> 32:25.080
-I think we'll have to wait to find out.
-Mm.

32:25.160 --> 32:26.560
[chuckling] Darling!

32:28.920 --> 32:32.320
My father asked me to tell you
you're expected on stage.

32:36.320 --> 32:38.560
[Carlos] Stay there, miss.
You owe me a dance.

32:42.720 --> 32:45.360
[Ricardo] I want to thank all of you
who have come here tonight

32:45.440 --> 32:51.960
to join with us in celebrating the opening
of Europe's largest telephone exchange.

32:52.040 --> 32:55.160
You all know that this hasn't been
an easy road, nor a short one.

32:55.240 --> 32:58.560
And that all these gray hairs
are due to that road.

32:59.640 --> 33:00.800
But we're finally here.

33:00.880 --> 33:03.920
And we wouldn't be
if it weren't for the person

33:04.000 --> 33:06.800
who was the driving force
behind this project.

33:06.880 --> 33:09.880
He's loyal, hardworking and honest.

33:09.960 --> 33:11.800
And it gives me great peace of mind

33:11.880 --> 33:15.840
to leave this company's future
in my son-in-law's hands,

33:15.920 --> 33:18.040
someone I consider my son,

33:18.120 --> 33:19.600
Francisco Gómez. Francisco.

33:19.680 --> 33:21.400
[crowd applauding]

33:27.640 --> 33:30.120
[Francisco] Thank you. Thank you.

33:30.200 --> 33:32.920
Ten years ago, I couldn't have imagined
being here today.

33:36.120 --> 33:37.960
I would've settled for a good job

33:38.040 --> 33:40.440
and a place to share
with the love of my life.

33:43.600 --> 33:46.200
Today, I have almost everything
I dreamt of.

33:47.760 --> 33:50.840
Almost, because one could always want
something more.

33:51.480 --> 33:54.400
Today is the beginning
of a new era for the company,

33:54.480 --> 33:56.240
one that will span the oceans.

33:57.080 --> 33:59.080
I am pleased to announce that tomorrow,

33:59.160 --> 34:02.000
this company is to make
its first intercontinental call.

34:02.720 --> 34:05.640
President Coolidge
and His Majesty Alfonso XIII

34:05.720 --> 34:10.120
will establish the first connection
between Spain and the United States.

34:18.520 --> 34:23.120
[Alba] <i>I'd tried to convince myself</i>
<i>that Francisco meant nothing to me.</i>

34:24.520 --> 34:28.080
<i>If I wanted to be free,</i>
<i>I couldn't be led by my heart.</i>

34:33.600 --> 34:36.520
<i>That night, I'd steal the money</i>
<i>from the company</i>

34:36.600 --> 34:39.600
<i>and run far away</i>
<i>from any ghost from the past.</i>

34:39.679 --> 34:43.520
<i>Good or bad, just to be myself.</i>

34:43.600 --> 34:45.880
Excuse me, miss. Your identification?

34:52.800 --> 34:54.239
That says "day shift."

34:54.320 --> 34:56.520
Only night shift employees
are allowed in.

34:56.600 --> 34:59.880
I know, but I'll just be a minute.
I left my purse in my locker.

34:59.960 --> 35:01.760
I'm sorry. You can get it tomorrow.

35:03.960 --> 35:05.840
But my house keys are in it.

35:08.120 --> 35:10.120
And there's no one I can call.

35:11.080 --> 35:12.480
Please do me this favor.

35:13.400 --> 35:15.800
Otherwise, I'll have to spend
the night on the street.

35:15.880 --> 35:17.680
I'll just be a moment.

35:47.920 --> 35:49.880
GENERAL DIRECTOR

36:05.920 --> 36:08.040
We must be the only two not invited
to the party.

36:08.120 --> 36:09.960
Julian says
even the stockroom workers went.

36:18.000 --> 36:20.600
-[upbeat song playing]
-I love this song. Do you know it?

36:21.760 --> 36:22.600
No.

36:22.680 --> 36:26.560
On a bad day, you can put it on
and forget everything. Listen.

36:26.640 --> 36:28.360
There are better songs.

36:28.440 --> 36:31.000
But if it helps you
forget your troubles...

36:31.080 --> 36:33.760
-How did you get out of the barracks?
-Through the window.

36:34.440 --> 36:36.480
A soldier's life is tough.

36:36.560 --> 36:39.040
It's a good thing
that the nights are much more fun.

36:39.120 --> 36:40.120
Let's dance.

37:04.800 --> 37:06.480
[both panting]

37:08.080 --> 37:11.920
<i>♪ And I can feel my heart skip ♪</i>

37:12.640 --> 37:14.560
<i>♪ Every time that I slip ♪</i>

37:15.160 --> 37:17.800
<i>♪ I wanna run away ♪</i>

37:41.000 --> 37:43.400
-[yells]
-Hey!

37:43.480 --> 37:44.560
Stop!

37:46.000 --> 37:47.320
[grunting]

37:57.480 --> 37:58.840
[grunts] Are you all right?

37:58.920 --> 38:00.400
[panting]

38:03.200 --> 38:06.400
I couldn't catch him, but I got
your purse. I think it's all there.

38:32.520 --> 38:33.680
[Carlota exclaims]

38:39.880 --> 38:44.440
[chuckling] I wonder what excuse I'll use
to get to my shift on time tomorrow.

38:44.520 --> 38:47.400
You can't keep doing this
for the rest of your life.

38:47.480 --> 38:49.200
I've got no choice.

38:49.280 --> 38:50.680
-Yes, you do.
-Really?

38:50.760 --> 38:53.280
-Marry me.
-[laughs] You're crazy.

38:53.360 --> 38:57.160
I didn't think I'd ask you either,
but it's the solution.

38:57.240 --> 39:00.320
-Oh, it's the solution, yes.
-[both chuckle]

39:01.560 --> 39:03.160
You wouldn't depend on your father.

39:03.240 --> 39:08.360
No, I'd depend on you, my husband.
The perfect definition of independence.

39:08.440 --> 39:10.520
You think I'd tell you what to do?

39:12.200 --> 39:13.320
You're drunk. I'm going.

39:13.400 --> 39:17.400
Yes, I'm drunk.
But I'm right. Think it over!

39:28.840 --> 39:30.160
[man] Let's go, Miguel!

39:32.160 --> 39:34.840
[Miguel] Good night! Wait up, guys.

39:49.600 --> 39:51.400
[faint clanging]

39:59.320 --> 40:00.520
[sighs]

40:06.680 --> 40:08.360
-[whispering] Don't make noise.
-Thanks.

40:08.440 --> 40:11.400
-I don't know where Miguel is.
-Don't worry.

40:11.480 --> 40:14.760
Both beds are for you.
I'm going home tomorrow.

40:14.840 --> 40:17.000
-Why?
-This isn't for me.

40:17.080 --> 40:19.800
I got lost on the subway,
broke my bag and got robbed.

40:19.880 --> 40:21.640
-Robbed?
-It doesn't matter.

40:21.720 --> 40:24.080
-I'm not staying.
-Marga!

40:24.160 --> 40:28.040
Do you know how long I faked
going to a sewing circle?

40:28.120 --> 40:31.600
One year. All that time,
I was really learning to type.

40:31.680 --> 40:34.880
I didn't want my parents
to know I wanted to work.

40:34.960 --> 40:36.920
I was afraid
they'd throw me out of the house.

40:38.360 --> 40:39.840
Gee. I'm sorry.

40:40.800 --> 40:41.960
Sorry? Why?

40:42.880 --> 40:44.040
I'm not sorry.

40:44.880 --> 40:47.560
Want to know the good part?
I'm not afraid anymore.

40:49.400 --> 40:52.600
I don't know how you can take it so well.

40:52.680 --> 40:54.080
What else can I do?

40:54.160 --> 40:57.760
Cry because my parents
prefer their ideas to who I am?

40:57.840 --> 41:01.360
No. There are two ways
to look at life...

41:01.440 --> 41:04.520
You can look on the negative side,
and cry and complain.

41:04.600 --> 41:08.560
Or look on the fun side,
enjoy it, laugh, and move forward.

41:08.640 --> 41:10.160
That's what I've chosen to do.

41:11.760 --> 41:14.360
Everything in life has its good side,
even Madrid.

41:15.440 --> 41:17.640
Even if you don't see it.

41:21.560 --> 41:23.680
Unless I rob that safe during the call...

41:25.600 --> 41:28.320
you'll have to find another home.

41:29.640 --> 41:30.800
[cat meows]

41:30.880 --> 41:32.880
Beltrán won't give me any more time.

41:34.520 --> 41:37.080
I either hand over the money tomorrow
at one o'clock or...

41:38.600 --> 41:40.200
This is my last chance.

41:41.960 --> 41:45.360
[newsboy] Extra! Extra!
First call to America today!

41:46.320 --> 41:48.960
Extra! Extra!
The king calls America today!

41:59.440 --> 42:02.440
-Mario, can I talk to you?
-I'm working, Ángeles. Not now.

42:02.520 --> 42:05.560
I was up all night worried about you.

42:06.160 --> 42:08.040
-Where were you?
-Walking.

42:09.720 --> 42:10.880
All night?

42:10.960 --> 42:13.160
All night. I had a lot to think about.

42:14.920 --> 42:18.320
-Mario--
-I won't argue about it here.

42:19.560 --> 42:23.680
I don't want to argue, just talk. Please.

42:34.640 --> 42:35.920
You want to talk?

42:36.520 --> 42:37.360
Talk.

42:38.320 --> 42:41.560
Mario, can't you understand

42:41.640 --> 42:44.080
that it bothers me
when you ask me to stop working?

42:44.160 --> 42:47.520
I can't believe this! What do you think?

42:47.600 --> 42:49.960
-That I don't know that you like your job?
-[shushes]

42:50.040 --> 42:52.400
And how hard it is
for you to leave all this?

42:53.120 --> 42:54.320
But we have a daughter,

42:54.400 --> 42:56.880
and I don't want a stranger
taking care of her.

42:56.960 --> 42:58.120
I want her mother to do it.

42:58.200 --> 43:01.400
Have you thought about how it torments me

43:01.480 --> 43:03.080
to not give my family what they deserve?

43:03.160 --> 43:06.160
I promised you everything,
that you'd live like a queen.

43:06.240 --> 43:10.600
And what did I get?
You're here all day, taking calls.

43:14.760 --> 43:18.680
You've convinced yourself
that it's right, and it's not.

43:21.360 --> 43:22.800
Let me make you happy.

43:24.280 --> 43:25.320
Please.

43:28.440 --> 43:30.040
Let's be the family we dreamt of being.

43:42.280 --> 43:43.320
STAFF FILE

43:43.400 --> 43:45.400
[door opens and closes]

43:46.600 --> 43:47.440
[Carlos] Good morning.

43:57.360 --> 44:00.640
-What are you looking for?
-The keys to the safe.

44:00.720 --> 44:04.120
Either I left them behind here,
or I lost them wherever I was last night.

44:04.200 --> 44:07.000
You should try drinking
two fewer glasses of brandy.

44:07.080 --> 44:10.440
-It'd be good for your memory.
-But terrible for my soul.

44:10.520 --> 44:12.480
My soul is free. It can't be chained.

44:13.480 --> 44:14.760
Right.

44:14.840 --> 44:16.960
You should try smiling sometime.

44:18.920 --> 44:19.960
Are you all right?

44:22.520 --> 44:24.920
-Do you remember Alba?
-Alba?

44:26.240 --> 44:27.560
[chuckles]

44:28.800 --> 44:30.560
[sighs]

44:30.640 --> 44:36.200
The love of your youth who vanished
without a word? Who ran away from you?

44:36.280 --> 44:37.880
Her? No.

44:38.880 --> 44:39.920
Yesterday, I thought I saw her.

44:40.000 --> 44:41.720
-Again?
-There was a strong resemblance.

44:42.320 --> 44:44.440
Francisco, people change in ten years.

44:45.480 --> 44:47.000
A lot. Look at you.

44:47.560 --> 44:49.680
[chuckles]

44:49.760 --> 44:52.760
Yes, you're right.
Forget it. It was stupid.

44:53.400 --> 44:55.560
Besides, there's things to be done.

44:57.080 --> 45:00.680
Elegant enough to be immortalized
next to His Majesty?

45:01.320 --> 45:04.480
Without those bags under your eyes,
I'd say you look quite respectable.

45:06.040 --> 45:08.040
There's a lot to do.

45:08.120 --> 45:09.960
-[stomps foot]
-What's on the agenda?

45:10.040 --> 45:13.760
First, inform Sara
about who's making the call.

45:13.840 --> 45:15.160
I've taken care of that already.

45:16.360 --> 45:17.520
Personally.

45:23.560 --> 45:25.840
-So?
-I'm sorry I'm late.

45:25.920 --> 45:28.320
-Changed your mind?
-What's going on?

45:28.400 --> 45:31.080
They're announcing which operator
will make the call.

45:31.160 --> 45:34.080
They'll give it to Ángeles.
She has the most experience.

45:34.160 --> 45:37.400
Ladies, we won't draw this out.

45:37.480 --> 45:40.920
Today, the transoceanic call
will be made between the king

45:41.000 --> 45:43.280
and the president of the United States.

45:43.360 --> 45:46.320
We're designating an operator
to make the call.

45:46.400 --> 45:47.760
It's a great responsibility,

45:47.840 --> 45:50.680
and I hope the chosen person
takes it as such.

45:51.280 --> 45:54.400
That person is... Lidia Aguilar.

45:55.080 --> 45:56.000
Me?

45:57.000 --> 45:58.320
I can't do it.

45:58.400 --> 45:59.760
Excuse me, Miss Aguilar?

45:59.840 --> 46:03.320
I'm new here at the company.
It's too much responsibility.

46:03.400 --> 46:06.520
-It should be Ángeles.
-I agree.

46:06.600 --> 46:09.160
It wasn't my decision to make.
It was management's.

46:09.240 --> 46:11.000
So I hope you can carry out your task.

46:12.040 --> 46:14.120
The operator protocol.

46:14.200 --> 46:16.120
Learn it as if your life depended on it.

46:16.200 --> 46:17.720
I can assure you, it does.

46:19.640 --> 46:23.160
The other switchboards
will be disconnected for ten minutes.

46:23.240 --> 46:26.560
So all you need to do
is witness this moment.

46:34.680 --> 46:36.880
-I won't do it.
-The protocol is simple.

46:36.960 --> 46:38.560
You managed the jacks well yesterday.

46:38.640 --> 46:40.640
-I don't mean--
-If anything goes wrong,

46:40.720 --> 46:42.360
other girls will cover you.

46:46.560 --> 46:49.240
This is a crucial moment
for the company, Carlos.

46:50.320 --> 46:52.280
You're jeopardizing it
to seduce an operator.

46:52.360 --> 46:54.040
You sound like my father.

46:55.360 --> 46:57.960
You think I'm doing this to seduce her?

46:58.040 --> 47:01.240
-Carlos--
-I like her image for the company.

47:01.320 --> 47:03.680
She's an ambitious girl.
I think she'll do it well.

47:03.760 --> 47:07.360
-Why didn't you ask me?
-I have to ask you about everything?

47:09.880 --> 47:12.080
Staff selection is my job.

47:14.800 --> 47:16.800
Trust me, please.

47:18.440 --> 47:20.840
Expectations are high among the media

47:20.920 --> 47:23.800
<i>here on the tenth floor</i>
<i>of the Telephone Company.</i>

47:23.880 --> 47:26.520
<i>Today, at exactly noon,</i>
<i>an event will take place</i>

47:26.600 --> 47:30.160
<i>that will mark</i>
<i>a before and after in history...</i>

47:30.240 --> 47:33.880
<i>The first intercontinental call</i>
<i>made from our country,</i>

47:33.960 --> 47:38.560
<i>involving two major figures</i>
<i>on either side of the Atlantic.</i>

47:40.680 --> 47:41.840
[crowd applauding]

47:41.920 --> 47:43.400
<i>His Majesty Alfonso XIII,</i>

47:43.480 --> 47:47.680
<i>whose arrival at the Telephone Company</i>
<i>we are about to witness,</i>

47:52.000 --> 47:54.360
<i>will speak to President Coolidge</i>
<i>in an exchange</i>

47:54.440 --> 47:58.280
<i>that will affirm the strong relationship</i>
<i>between our countries.</i>

48:01.560 --> 48:03.880
[Alba] <i>I wasn't afraid of the challenge.</i>

48:03.960 --> 48:06.440
<i>But it would make my objective</i>
<i>harder to achieve.</i>

48:09.440 --> 48:14.400
<i>While the whole world was wrapped up</i>
<i>in that great historical event...</i>

48:15.960 --> 48:17.640
<i>I'd rob the safe.</i>

48:18.160 --> 48:22.920
<i>I'd put an end to Beltrán's blackmail</i>
<i>and flee in search of a new life...</i>

48:24.360 --> 48:26.000
<i>far from my past,</i>

48:26.720 --> 48:29.600
<i>and far from the man</i>
<i>who was once the love of my life.</i>

48:44.520 --> 48:47.320
-It's time, Father.
-Very well.

48:47.400 --> 48:50.920
When you wish, Your Majesty.
The world awaits.

49:10.000 --> 49:13.080
Good morning. Telephone Company.
How may I help you?

49:13.160 --> 49:15.760
Yes, operator?

49:15.840 --> 49:20.480
Could you please connect me
with Washington, United States?

49:20.560 --> 49:23.480
<i>Number 0002, with the president.</i>

49:23.560 --> 49:25.400
Of course, Your Majesty.

49:25.480 --> 49:28.560
I'm connecting you now.
One moment, please.

50:04.160 --> 50:05.280
I've lost the line.

50:06.240 --> 50:08.600
[Francisco] We checked the circuits.
There must be a signal.

50:08.680 --> 50:09.840
[Sara] You're doing something wrong.

50:11.520 --> 50:12.880
[Alba] There's no signal.

50:12.960 --> 50:16.960
Jack one to jack two... It's off.

50:25.640 --> 50:27.120
[panting]

50:37.600 --> 50:38.720
[in English] Hello?

50:39.640 --> 50:41.240
Washington, DC?

50:50.800 --> 50:55.080
[Alba] <i>An historic day.</i>
<i>A triumph for communications.</i>

50:55.160 --> 50:58.480
<i>The world in the hands of a woman,</i>
<i>a switchboard operator.</i>

50:58.560 --> 51:00.440
[Alfonso XIII in English]
Thank you very much, Mr. President.

51:00.520 --> 51:02.240
[Alba] <i>Everyone was celebrating</i>
<i>this incredible event</i>

51:02.320 --> 51:04.880
<i>and felt they were part</i>
<i>of a new world...</i>

51:04.960 --> 51:08.240
<i>But some women began to understand</i>
<i>that the new world</i>

51:08.320 --> 51:11.400
<i>wasn't as idyllic or as simple</i>
<i>as they would have liked...</i>

51:12.160 --> 51:16.120
<i>It would involve family sacrifices</i>
<i>and loneliness...</i>

51:17.160 --> 51:19.720
<i>for independence always comes at a price.</i>

51:20.960 --> 51:22.920
<i>For Gimena, it was her life.</i>

51:23.720 --> 51:27.120
<i>For me, it was being condemned</i>
<i>to break the rules.</i>

51:27.200 --> 51:32.840
<i>♪ But I know</i>
<i>Once in a while we will find ♪</i>

51:32.920 --> 51:37.360
<i>♪ The sound of your heart beats</i>
<i>With mine ♪</i>

51:37.800 --> 51:44.080
<i>♪ And when it's time</i>
<i>I'll leave the ocean behind ♪</i>

51:49.880 --> 51:51.880
<i>♪ So I'll look ♪</i>

51:52.800 --> 51:56.320
<i>♪ Out for a lighthouse ♪</i>

51:56.400 --> 51:58.400
<i>♪ See through the fog ♪</i>

51:58.480 --> 52:01.160
<i>♪ Search the horizon ♪</i>

52:01.840 --> 52:02.840
Stop.

52:03.160 --> 52:06.440
<i>♪ Once in a while we will find ♪</i>

52:06.520 --> 52:11.080
<i>♪ The sound of your heart beats</i>
<i>With mine ♪</i>

52:13.920 --> 52:15.000
I know who you are.

52:22.440 --> 52:25.000
Ten years isn't long enough
to forget you...

52:26.600 --> 52:27.600
Alba.

52:37.720 --> 52:40.360
<i>♪ You've seen the light</i>
<i>How it's shining bright, shining down ♪</i>

52:40.440 --> 52:42.800
<i>♪ Through the clouds</i>
<i>Making everything come alive ♪</i>

52:42.880 --> 52:46.240
<i>♪ Making everything wrong feel right</i>
<i>Making everything loose feel tight ♪</i>

52:46.320 --> 52:48.440
<i>♪ Like the stars in the heavens</i>
<i>Lined up ♪</i>

52:48.520 --> 52:50.920
<i>♪ Like I'm the only one on the set</i>
<i>There's no more feeling like it's over ♪</i>

52:51.000 --> 52:53.600
<i>♪ But the only thing that's over</i>
<i>I'm no longer standing over ♪</i>

52:53.680 --> 52:56.560
<i>♪ I don't know what's the use, the use</i>
<i>They no longer can refuse me ♪</i>

52:58.360 --> 53:01.040
<i>♪ 'Cause now I'm taking control ♪</i>

53:01.120 --> 53:07.920
<i>♪ And now, tonight</i>
<i>I'm getting out, out, out of this place ♪</i>

53:08.680 --> 53:13.760
<i>♪ And I'm not falling behind</i>
<i>I'll hold the winning trophy ♪</i>

53:13.840 --> 53:17.200
<i>♪ At the end of this race ♪</i>

53:17.280 --> 53:20.640
<i>♪ I'll be dancing in the rain</i>
<i>I'll be drinking champagne! ♪</i>

53:21.640 --> 53:24.800
<i>♪ This is my night ♪</i>

53:25.840 --> 53:28.280
<i>♪ And I own it ♪</i>

53:28.360 --> 53:32.480
<i>♪ Say yeah ♪</i>

